dc_description_s: This layer is a georeferenced raster image of the historic paper map entitled: Comitatus Nottinghamiensis; sive Nottingham Shire. It was published by J. Janssonius ca. [1646?] Scale [ca. 1:197,000]. 5 Milliaria Anglica = 4,7 cm. Title in Latin and English, place names in English, French text on verso. The image inside the map neatline is georeferenced to the surface of the earth and fit to the 'British National Grid' coordinate system. All map collar and inset information is also available as part of the raster image, including any inset maps, profiles, statistical tables, directories, text, illustrations, index maps, legends, or other information associated with the principal map. This map shows features such as drainage, cities and other human settlements, territorial boundaries, shoreline features, and more. Relief shown pictorially. Includes also wapentakes, cartouche decorated with figures of peasants, in upper left corner are coats of arms of local nobility, in upper right the coat of arms of England. This layer is part of a selection of digitally scanned and georeferenced historic maps from the Harvard Map Collection. These maps typically portray both natural and manmade features. The selection represents a range of originators, ground condition dates, scales, and map purposes.
